SHS Enrollment Database Documentation (cdonhs_shs_database_enrollment)

This database is for a Senior High School enrollment & elective selection system. It stores:

user accounts (admin/teacher/student)

student application records (Form-like profile)

official enrollment status per school year

track assignment (Academic / TechPro)

subject catalog (old subject + new curriculum subject_new)

subject offerings per school year / grade / semester / section

student subject enlistment and elective choices

The system supports core subjects + track electives.

1) Main Concepts
A) User vs Student

users = login accounts (username/password/role)

students = enrolled student entity linked to a user (students.user_id)

B) Application vs Enrollment

student_applications = full personal data + requirements uploads + application status (Pending/Approved/etc.)

students = final enrollment record (Active/Graduated/etc.) with school_year + enlistment status

So:

Student submits application → goes to student_applications

Admin approves → student gets created/activated in students

C) Track and Cluster

tracks = only Academic or TechPro

clusters = elective groupings under a track (e.g., STEM cluster is now just “Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics” without “STEM label” in UI)

D) Subjects & Offerings

You currently have two catalogs:

subject

looks like your legacy/old subject list (many duplicates because before it was strand-based)

now altered to support track/cluster fields, but data is still old.

subject_new

your new curriculum subject list (Strengthened SHS mapping)

already mapped to track + cluster + grade recommendation + NC equivalents

Offerings:

subject_offerings = when a subject is available for enrollment
It depends on: school_year, grade_level, semester, and optional section_id, with optional slots.

E) Student Enrollment & Electives

student_subjects = the student’s “enlisted subjects” for a school year
can hold status (Pending/Enrolled/Completed etc.) and references subject_id and optionally offering_id

student_electives = separate table specifically for elective selections by offering
(student chooses an offering, per semester, per school year)

2) Table-by-Table Meaning
activation_settings

Feature toggles:

“Student Enrollment” ON/OFF

“Form 137/138 Page” ON/OFF

“Student Progress Page” ON/OFF

“Teacher Registration” ON/OFF

Frontend should read these to hide/disable pages.

users

Login credentials + role:

role_id links to roles (Admin / Student / Teacher)

first_login flag can force password change on first login

status allows disabling users

roles

Defines allowed roles.

teachers

Teacher profile linked to users.

students

Official enrollment identity:

linked to users and student_applications

enrollment_status: Active/Inactive/Graduated/Transferred

enlistment_status: Not Enlisted / Pending / Enlisted / Rejected / Promoted / Finished

school_year indicates the SY of this enrollment record

student_applications

Full application form data:

personal info, parents, address

learning modality flags (blended, online, modular, etc.)

uploaded file paths (PSA birth certificate, Form 138, etc.)

approval status + remarks

tracks

Two entries: Academic, TechPro.

student_track

Assigns each student to a track:

1 student = 1 track (because student_id is primary key)

This is how you decide what electives they can see.

clusters

Elective groupings:

Core cluster has track_id = NULL (shared)

Other clusters belong to Academic or TechPro

Frontend uses clusters to group elective subjects.

subject_new

New curriculum subject catalog:

track_id can be NULL for core subjects

cluster_id required

subject_type: CORE or ELECTIVE

recommended_grade_level: ‘11’, ‘12’, or ‘11/12’

nc_equivalent: NC II / NC III etc for TechPro

is_required: marks must-take subjects (ex: Work Immersion for TechPro)

is_active: allows you to hide/deprecate subjects without deleting

subject

This is your existing subject catalog used by your old enrollment records.
Because student_subjects.subject_id references subject.subject_id, you must not delete/replace these rows unless you migrate old enrollments.

subject_offerings

This is the “schedule catalog”:

subject offered in a given SY, grade, semester, optionally section

supports slots

is_active to open/close offerings

Use this table for enrollment selection UI.

student_subjects

This is the “student enlistment list”:

tracks the subject a student is taking (per school year)

status supports Pending/Enrolled/Completed/Dropped/etc.

can optionally reference a specific offering (offering_id)

This is your “official record of what subjects a student is registered in”.

student_electives

This is “student elective choices”:

links student to subject_offerings

includes semester + school_year

unique constraint prevents selecting same offering twice

This table is used when you want “elective selection” separate from the official subject enlistment.

section

Class sections:

includes grade_level

has both strand_id and track_id (currently most are NULL for track_id)

your DB is in transition: old sections were strand-based

If you move fully to track-based, you will stop using strand_id.

strands, student_strand, archived_student_strand

Legacy strand system:

strands list (STEM/ABM/HUMSS/GAS/TVL...)

student_strand is the student’s strand assignment

archived_student_strand stores history (promotion/transfer/manual)

If the goal is “remove strand labels shown”, the frontend should stop reading strands and instead read track/cluster.

3) Recommended System Flow (Frontend + Backend)
Step 1: Application

Frontend

Student fills up application form

uploads required docs

Backend

POST /applications

saves to student_applications with status Pending

Admin

PATCH /applications/:id/approve

creates or activates users + students

Step 2: Track Assignment

Frontend (Admin)

choose student’s track (Academic/TechPro)

Backend

POST /students/:id/track

upsert into student_track

Step 3: Show Subjects (New Curriculum)

When student opens “Electives / Enlistment” page:

Backend should return:

core subjects (cluster_id = 1) from subject_new

electives based on track:

if track Academic → subject_new.track_id = 1

if track TechPro → subject_new.track_id = 2

group by clusters

Example endpoints

GET /students/:id/curriculum

returns { coreSubjects, electiveClusters }

Step 4: Offerings (what can be selected)

Subjects exist in catalog, but selection should be from offerings.

Backend

GET /offerings?school_year=2026-2027&grade_level=11&semester=1&track_id=2

join offerings → subject_new or subject (choose one catalog consistently)

filter by student track

Step 5: Student selects electives

Frontend

Student chooses from available offerings

Backend

POST /students/:id/electives

insert into student_electives

Optional: also create official entries in student_subjects (recommended)

for each chosen offering, insert into student_subjects with status Pending/Enrolled

This makes progress tracking easier.

Step 6: Enlistment / Finalize

Backend

POST /students/:id/enlist

validate:

all required subjects selected (core + required electives)

elective limit per semester (your policy)

slots not exceeded

set students.enlistment_status = 'Enlisted'

4) Frontend Pages You Can Build
Student Portal

Dashboard (activation toggles)

Application Form (if not approved)

Track & Curriculum view (read-only)

Elective selection page (by offerings)

My Subjects (from student_subjects)

Progress page (if enabled)

Admin Portal

Applications list + approve/reject

Students list + assign track

Subject catalog management (activate/deactivate subjects)

Create offerings per SY/semester/section/slots

Monitor elective selections

Enlistment approvals / finalization

Teacher Portal

Advisory class list (if you connect teacher_advisory)

Student progress view (read student_subjects)

5) Important Notes / Warnings

Don’t delete old subject rows
student_subjects.subject_id references them. Deleting breaks history.

You are mid-migration:

legacy: strands (student_strand, strands)

new: tracks + clusters (student_track, clusters, subject_new)
UI should choose one “source of truth” depending on curriculum year.

To “remove STEM/ABM/HUMSS labels”:

UI should stop using strands table for display

show tracks.track_name + clusters.cluster_name instead

